Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.86,0:01:40.32,Top,,0,0,0,,Isabel, do hurry or we’ll be late for class.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.80,0:01:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, I’ll be done in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.17,0:01:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it looks odd somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.67,0:01:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it? I think it’s lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.74,0:01:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's lovely by default,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.64,0:01:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you tie it like this, \Nit looks even prettier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.05,0:01:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,See, it’s a bit crooked, isn’t it? {?? not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.85,0:02:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I simply can’t go to class \Nuntil it looks right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.77,0:02:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.42,0:02:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All she ever thinks about is how she looks. {lit: inside her head only fashion}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.36,0:02:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There, that does it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.33,0:02:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.90,0:02:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You look smashing, Alison.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.65,0:02:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirror, mirror, on the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.37,0:02:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who is the fairest girl of all?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.93,0:02:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, it’s Alison, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.23,0:02:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I’m thrilled!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.77,0:02:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really stand there \Nand say that every day? {to the mirror}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.70,0:02:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.14,0:02:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.34,0:02:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.01,0:03:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not really the prettiest of them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.33,0:03:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.82,0:03:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There she is, the prettiest girl of St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that’s Madeleine...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.47,0:03:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,from the fifth form.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.27,0:03:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s like a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.14,0:03:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Like an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.71,0:03:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I wish I could be like Madeleine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.01,0:03:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, you're one of the few \Nwho have a flair for fashion here at St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Really, Madeleine?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.33,0:03:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re quite sweet too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.57,0:04:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I adore beautiful things—\Nwhether clothes or friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.81,0:04:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We could be friends, you and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.35,0:04:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Alison, why don’t you start \Nby doing as I say from today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.15,0:04:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.12,0:04:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you must look after your nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.92,0:04:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nail varnish? {/Manicure}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.36,0:04:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Won’t the teachers scold us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.56,0:04:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If they find out, \Nthey might call in my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.04,0:04:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all, just wear it secretly, \Nonly when you go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.40,0:04:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.40,0:04:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, dear, that ribbon won’t do, \Nit doesn’t suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.84,0:04:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.58,0:04:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Your waist is too thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.74,0:04:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.08,0:04:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Until you trim five centimetres off your waist, \Nthat ribbon won’t suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.19,0:04:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, you must lose weight, \Nif you want to be a beautiful girl like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.43,0:04:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Madeleine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, biscuits!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.74,0:05:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Some chocolate as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison should be here any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.20,0:05:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, you girls are horrible, \Nhiding them from me! {/doing it in secret}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.52,0:05:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know full well \Nhow fond I am of sweets!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.28,0:05:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,May I?" {??? choudai most likely, but that tone doesn't sound like a question, and that gesture doesn't hint on it either}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.98,0:05:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a natural at it! {???????? no clue at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, we brought you some chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.52,0:05:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Chocolate?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.89,0:05:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Eating sweets before bed is shameful. {contempt; scorn; disdain; despising; looking down on; slighting}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.06,0:05:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.33,0:05:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I’ve decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.73,0:05:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,From today, I shall never eat sweets again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.82,0:05:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.27,0:05:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I will lose weight, whatever it takes! \NJust watch—Alison’s Grand Diet Plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, meatloaf! {???}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.55,0:05:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Bon appétit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.10,0:05:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That was delicious. {meaning she's done eating already}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.22,0:05:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, are you finished already?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.85,0:05:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I had tomatoes and celery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.99,0:05:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Only that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.41,0:06:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Meat is fatty, eggs and margarine are high in calories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.86,0:06:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat it all and you’ll end up \Nlike a great fat snowman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.95,0:06:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? A snowman? Don’t be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.45,0:06:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no laughing matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.47,0:06:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you all want to be beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.01,0:06:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.37,0:06:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There! That one mouthful \Nwill make your legs fat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.46,0:06:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Swallow that, and Jimmy will hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.02,0:06:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, they say boys loathe fat girls most of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re not pretty, \Nboys won’t even glance at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.76,0:06:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense! Forget diets and let’s just eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.33,0:06:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow I’ve lost my appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.37,0:06:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.33,0:06:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll go on a diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.17,0:06:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.30,0:06:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So will I.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.21,0:06:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.52,0:06:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That was tasty! {sounds silly in english setting but idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.18,0:06:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.88,0:06:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.53,0:06:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, they're all hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.18,0:06:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m eating mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.49,0:07:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel? Not you too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.36,0:07:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.13,0:07:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.29,0:07:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe a little. \NJust a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.73,0:07:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ham is a hundred and fifty calories...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Cake’s two hundred, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.25,0:07:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Eat that and you’re a pig.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.51,0:07:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.58,0:07:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.01,0:07:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, I’ll resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.25,0:07:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.52,0:07:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.89,0:07:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re all late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.85,0:07:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Even thought the match \Nagainst St. Jullia’s is so soon. {it was most likely "st. Julian's" originally, but at 19:01 they spell it as "jullia" (by mistake, obv), and this school is never brought up again, so i'd rather compromise for this one episode}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.28,0:07:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of lacrosse practice, \Ntheir heads are full of...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.83,0:07:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,diets, diets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.90,0:07:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! Resist, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.30,0:07:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’ve never once lost to St. Jullia’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.01,0:07:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so it'll be fine even without practice... \Nis what I would've liked to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we go fetch them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.94,0:07:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.08,0:07:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.15,0:08:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.88,0:08:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The first formers leave their meals \Nhalf-finished so often lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.45,0:08:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the food doesn’t suit them? {their tastes}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.19,0:08:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan my menus with such care, \Nhoping to please them, for days on end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.69,0:08:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night’s beef stew—\Nwhen I said I wanted to be a cook,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.10,0:08:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother stayed up all night \Nto teach me to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.57,0:08:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the taste of home for me. {/of memories}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.09,0:08:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the young ones \Ndon’t find it good any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.48,0:08:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls, it’s time for practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.65,0:08:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s with your faces?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.03,0:08:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can’t you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.36,0:08:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re doing beauty packs. {lit: doing packs - no idea what this should be properly called in english}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.89,0:08:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It tightens the skin...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.56,0:08:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes you lovelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.56,0:08:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I never!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.27,0:08:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’ve time for that, \Nyou’ve time for lacrosse practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.15,0:09:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the use of being good at lacrosse for a girl? \NIt doesn’t make you pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.07,0:09:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important thing for a girl is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.66,0:09:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whether she’s beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.11,0:09:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.71,0:09:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, that’s what matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, look, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.72,0:09:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think your dieting \Nmakes you beautiful at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.52,0:09:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.09,0:09:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the cooks, all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.18,0:09:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.53,0:09:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day they picture our happy faces
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.69,0:09:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and put their hearts into every dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.87,0:09:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,To waste their food so thoughtlessly... {/leave behind}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.51,0:09:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t put it well, but... \Neven if you diet and look pretty,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.62,0:09:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can’t be considerate of others, \Nthat’s the most shameful thing of all for a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.13,0:09:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you’re quite right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.80,0:09:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, that was splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.73,0:10:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, can you answer that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.50,0:10:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.01,0:10:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is just jealous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.06,0:10:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.07,0:10:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Her nose is flat, and her figure’s so dumpy \Nyou can't even tell where her waist is. {having no waist; undefined (waist); rectangle (body shape); straight/cylindrical }
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.58,0:10:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Alison...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.08,0:10:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She’ll never be pretty, diet or no diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.92,0:10:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She was born plain, \Nthat’s why she says such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.12,0:10:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Alison!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.86,0:10:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, that was cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.53,0:10:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you’re my cousin, \Nyou’re simply awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.34,0:10:57.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,Oh God, why is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.39,0:11:01.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,Some are born beautiful, others not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.96,0:11:03.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,Why must it be so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.88,0:11:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.88,0:11:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, Pat, what’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.18,0:11:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, we're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.64,0:11:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We're ashamed to be Alison’s cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.21,0:11:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.50,0:11:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s conceited and frivolous, \Nbut at heart she isn’t a bad girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.45,0:11:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She must be regretting what she said by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.82,0:11:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t ask you to forgive her, but at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.03,0:11:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all right! I’m not upset in the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.16,0:11:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.50,0:11:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for worrying about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.57,0:11:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean to do my very best \Nin the match against St. Jullia’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.51,0:11:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m off for a run. Well then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.48,0:11:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.03,0:12:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But... But...! {meaning "but I was right" - she's conflicted because she thinks herself right, but not fully}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.19,0:12:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.29,0:12:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s been down ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.82,0:12:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I must apologise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.93,0:12:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But how to begin...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.80,0:12:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls, you’ve seemed off these past few weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:12:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.01,0:13:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.18,0:13:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow is the lacrosse match against St. Jullia’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.49,0:13:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.99,0:13:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it’s no good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.44,0:13:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to lose \Nat least three centimetres more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.66,0:13:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At least three more?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.77,0:13:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! A cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.94,0:13:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mind if I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.27,0:13:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're not!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.04,0:13:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right for me. \NI never put on weight, whatever I eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.75,0:13:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.98,0:13:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes, you’ve got a lacrosse match tomorrow, haven’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.45,0:13:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.51,0:13:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Lacrosse is dreadful—muddy, bruising.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.29,0:13:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Positively barbaric.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.49,0:13:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Feign an illness and stay out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.51,0:13:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? B-But feigning illness is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.53,0:13:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Won’t you do as I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.81,0:14:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! The inter-school match is here. {?????? noi clue what's that gankousei}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.14,0:14:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s only St. Jullia’s. Easy peasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.56,0:14:09.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,What shall I do? \NI can’t pretend to be ill...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.88,0:14:13.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I can’t bear to have Madeleine dislike me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.25,0:14:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong, Alison?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.07,0:14:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You look under the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.79,0:14:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it’s just...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.03,0:14:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel faint...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.73,0:14:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Better go to the infirmary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.80,0:14:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Will she be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.20,0:14:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let her be. That’s Alison for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.70,0:14:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.85,0:14:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it, Alison?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.80,0:14:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Show me the thermometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.42,0:14:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.86,0:14:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness me! Thirty-nine degrees!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.73,0:14:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No chance of lacrosse for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.23,0:14:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll tell Miss Roberts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.84,0:15:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.67,0:15:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What, it's Kathleen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.71,0:15:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, you’re only pretending.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.26,0:15:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What? How did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.38,0:15:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, don’t tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.77,0:15:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I won’t, but you ought to own up \Nto the mistress yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.39,0:15:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t possibly, not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.66,0:15:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But Alison, if you become the sort of girl who can lie \Nwithout a qualm... that would be dreadful!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.40,0:15:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s none of your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.67,0:15:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is. I like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.14,0:15:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t bear to think you’d cheat and not care.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.81,0:15:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, muster up your courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.98,0:15:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.18,0:15:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry, I’ve no right to preach. {lit: I said something great/pretentious}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.00,0:16:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.66,0:16:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the pretence work?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.97,0:16:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Madeleine, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.50,0:16:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.34,0:16:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don’t be angry, \Nbut I think I was wrong to feign illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.71,0:16:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Do you mean to tell the mistresses now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.81,0:16:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.38,0:16:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you, of all people, \Nhave that kind of courage? {lit: you, the spoiled child, have that courage?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.42,0:16:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.18,0:16:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Madeleine, there’s something I must ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Miss Lewis? Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.66,0:16:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I found nail varnish in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.96,0:16:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember ever saying \Nthat such items were allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.63,0:16:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I dislike to do it, \Nbut I must call in your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.05,0:16:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents? \NB-But it isn’t mine, it belongs to Alison.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.31,0:16:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.84,0:16:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,She forced her way \Ninto my room, though I said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.61,0:16:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll find more of it in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.83,0:16:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Madeleine, how could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.35,0:16:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,E-Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.12,0:17:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You know, our Alison
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.76,0:17:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is an inveterate liar, who pretends to be ill to shirk lacrosse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,P-Please, Madeleine!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.40,0:17:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg of you! If my parents \Nare to scold me, I’d sooner die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.17,0:17:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, back to your room, Madeleine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.17,0:17:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.95,0:17:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.42,0:17:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Only God and your own heart \Nknow the truth of the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.82,0:17:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I shan’t press you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.06,0:17:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is for you to decide. \NThink it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.87,0:17:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.57,0:17:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.89,0:17:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, so you have a fever?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.34,0:17:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest well, Alison.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.61,0:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There, lie down in bed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.18,0:18:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if something’s wrong with Alison.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.18,0:18:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... But never mind, \Nit’s time for the match. {that un is actually "I wonder too"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.53,0:18:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.64,0:18:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Alison?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.24,0:18:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I must muster up my courage sometimes too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.33,0:18:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me watch the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.83,0:18:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's hopeless! \NI’m too hungry to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.66,0:18:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Joan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.96,0:18:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t run another step.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.34,0:18:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No... No more!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.97,0:18:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm so done...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.12,0:18:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray! St. Clare’s are total pushovers! {novice; greenhorn; squirt; worthless person​}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.07,0:18:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No courage at all. Easy peasy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.68,0:19:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, c'est abominable!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.88,0:19:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you lose to St. Jullia’s, \NI’ll set you piles of homework!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.87,0:19:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong with everyone? \NThey are in such a poor shape. {lit: moving is bad}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.82,0:19:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the dieting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.49,0:19:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ve been eating only one meal a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.36,0:19:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness gracious! {/how terrible}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.49,0:19:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What a terrible strain \Nfor a growing girl! {lit: for you in growth period, such a thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.06,0:19:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder they’re faint.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.30,0:19:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, Hilary, \Ntake over from Janet and Doris.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.67,0:19:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.89,0:19:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen! Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.91,0:19:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! Splendid, Kathleen! {???}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.05,0:19:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to pass the ball to Kathleen more! {?? lit: collect the ball with kath}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.10,0:19:59.33,Thought,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.92,0:20:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! I can’t move another step...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.42,0:20:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, c'est abominable!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.47,0:20:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll replace her with... {lit: the replacement player is...}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.74,0:20:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll play instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.04,0:20:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison? But aren’t you ill?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.43,0:20:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.58,0:20:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m really...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.75,0:20:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m really not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.62,0:20:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was pretending.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.75,0:20:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.12,0:20:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.65,0:20:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, let me play.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.06,0:20:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Roberts!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.44,0:20:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're asking you as well! \NPlease let Alison play!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.81,0:20:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, Isabel, Pat...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.25,0:20:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, stay strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.88,0:20:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up yet! {????}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.85,0:20:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison, pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.22,0:20:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot, Alison!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.46,0:20:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-five...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.86,0:21:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to twenty-four!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.66,0:21:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We just scraped through.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.26,0:21:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly disgraced St. Clare’s entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.82,0:21:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, look at that! Alison, that’s hardly the look \Nof the smartest girl in St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.84,0:21:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But I take my hat off to you. {/I changed my mind about you}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.64,0:21:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It took courage to admit \Nyou’d been malingering.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.34,0:21:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a tiny bit, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.80,0:21:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m ashamed of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,K-Kathleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.82,0:21:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.95,0:21:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.02,0:21:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty hair, good style, or a slim figure \Naren’t nearly enough on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.73,0:21:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,True beauty shines from the whole person—\Nkindness, honest effort—like you, Kathleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.97,0:21:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.36,0:21:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's decided! \NMiss St. Clare’s is Kathleen!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.88,0:21:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, and here’s your reward \Nfor winning the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.65,0:22:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless some of you still want to diet! {and won't eat}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! How unkind of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.19,0:22:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had quite enough of dieting.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.08,0:22:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tuck in! {itadakimasu}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.04,0:22:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Marvellous! These sweets \Nare seriously irresistible! {????}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.73,0:22:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, what bliss! \NTo eat one’s fill!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.27,0:22:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alison!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.90,0:22:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that’s mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.50,0:22:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought you’d grown up a bit... {??? sounds like kath, probably saying it to ali in the meaning "stop being so childish to be crazy about sweets"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.22,0:23:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, something awful’s happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.75,0:23:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A boy turned up saying Binks was his, \Nand he’s taken him away! {? ko could be a girl and from this i can't be sure}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.67,0:23:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You can’t be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.29,0:23:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true! He even knew his name was Binks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.06,0:23:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn’t make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.56,0:23:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it was Kathleen who named him Binks!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.00,0:23:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.00,0:23:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, we must get him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.82,0:23:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. For Kathleen’s sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.60,0:23:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, for Kathleen!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.27,0:23:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.91,0:24:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"Give Back Binks!" {ビンクスを返して!}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.27,0:24:05.23,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 25 \NGive Back Binks! {ビンクスを返して!}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.17,0:24:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t miss it!
